# CSS  - 12

## 


###  (Media Queries)
 CSS3  CSS 

****
```css
@media mediatype and|not|only (mediafeature and|or|not mediafeature) {
  /* CSS  */
}
```
- `mediatype` `screen` (), `print` (), `all` ()
- `and|not|only`
- `mediafeature` `width`, `max-width`, `min-width`, `orientation` (landscape | portrait), `resolution` 

** (Breakpoints)**

- : `max-width: 575.98px`
- : `min-width: 576px` and `max-width: 767.98px`
- : `min-width: 768px` and `max-width: 991.98px`
- : `min-width: 992px` and `max-width: 1199.98px`
- : `min-width: 1200px`

****
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="box">Box 1</div>
  <div class="box">Box 2</div>
  <div class="box">Box 3</div>
</div>
<style>
body {
  font-size: 16px;
}
.container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row; /*  */
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  padding: 10px;
}
.box {
  background-color: lightblue;
  border: 1px solid blue;
  padding: 20px;
  margin: 10px;
  flex: 1;
  text-align: center;
}

/*  768px  */
@media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
  body {
    font-size: 14px;
  }
  .container {
    flex-direction: column; /*  */
  }
  .box {
    background-color: lightcoral;
  }
}

/*  480px  */
@media screen and (max-width: 480px) {
  body {
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  .box {
    padding: 10px;
    background-color: lightgreen;
  }
}
</style>
```

### rem
`rem` (root em)  (`<html>`)  `font-size`
 `font-size` `rem` 

****
1.  ** (Viewport)** HTML  `<head>`  viewport meta 
    ```html
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no">
    ```
2.  **** JavaScript  `<html>`  `font-size` 750px 100 1rem  `750px / 100 = 7.5px` () `font-size`

**JavaScript  `font-size` **
```html
<head>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>REM Adaptaion</title>
  <script>
    (function(doc, win) {
      var docEl = doc.documentElement,
          resizeEvt = 'orientationchange' in window ? 'orientationchange' : 'resize',
          recalc = function() {
            var clientWidth = docEl.clientWidth;
            if (!clientWidth) return;
            //  750px 1rem = 100px (750px)
            //  font-size = clientWidth / (750 / 100) = clientWidth / 7.5
            // 101rem = 75px
            //  font-size = clientWidth / 10
